Package io.jstach.rainbowgum

Interface LogEvent.Builder

Enclosing interface:
LogEvent
public static sealed interface LogEvent.Builder
A builder to create events by calling LogRouter.eventBuilder(String, Level). log() should be called at the very end otherwise the event will not be logged. Because of potential future optimizations (see API note) It is best to assume this builder returns a different builder on every setter call even if it may not currently!
API Note
unless the builder gets marked for escape analysis the static LogEvent factory methods are more likely to be superior in performance. EA is tricky business and often requires the object be small enough and should not leave the method it is constructed in but the JDK is continuously getting better optimizing immutable objects. Thus it is best to assume this builder will return a different builder on every call.
